    time: 1760455500.012771,
    opcode: 1,
    data: '{"type":"input","data":"A user can grow unclaimedFlux without bound by repeatedly creating a new â€œdustâ€ veNFT, merging the previous veNFT into the new one, and calling reset again each time, all without ever voting. First approve BPT for the VotingEscrow contract, create an initial lock to obtain a first token (the previous token), and call Voter.reset on it to establish a baseline unclaimedFlux value. Then for a fixed number of iterations such as ten, create a new dust lock to obtain a next token, call VotingEscrow.merge from the previous token into the next token so that FluxToken.mergeFlux transfers the accumulated unclaimedFlux and zeroes the source, call Voter.reset on the next token to accrue again, and read unclaimedFlux to confirm it strictly increases compared to the prior reading. After the loop, assert that the final unclaimedFlux is roughly linear in the number of iterations relative to the baseline (for example final is at least ten times the baseline). Proving the ever-increasing unclaimedFlux is sufficient; claiming ERC-20 Flux is not required."}',
