    data: '{"type":"planner-step","data":{"tag_type":"planner_step","timestamp":"2025-10-14T15:26:28.505454+00:00","step_number":4,"content":"Step 3. (Iterative Merging Loop â€“ 10 iterations)\\n\\nFor iterations i = 1 to 10, execute the following sub-steps:\\n\\nA. Create a â€œdustâ€ lock (new token).\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢â€‚Action: Call VotingEscrow.createLock to create a new â€œdustâ€ lock.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: VotingEscrow (\\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"createLock\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [dustAmount, shortLockDuration, maxLockEnabled]  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒFor example: dustAmount = a very small amount (e.g. 1 wei or another minimal value that is accepted),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒshortLockDuration = a valid lock duration that is less than MAXTIME but ensures the lock remains active (and greater than the current block.timestamp),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒmaxLockEnabled = false  \\nâ€¢â€‚Rationale: This â€œnext tokenâ€ will be used as the target of a merge so that its unclaimedFlux can be increased.\\n\\nB. Merge the previous veNFT into the new one.\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢â€‚Action: Call VotingEscrow.merge to merge the previously created token (from the previous iteration; for the first iteration use tokenId_baseline) into the new â€œdustâ€ token.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: VotingEscrow (\\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"merge\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [prevTokenId, newTokenId]  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒWhere prevTokenId is the token ID from the previous round and newTokenId is the one just created.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Rationale: Inside VotingEscrow.merge the call IFluxToken(FLUX).mergeFlux(_from, _to) transfers unclaimedFlux from the source (prevTokenId) to the target (newTokenId) and then wipes out the sourceâ€™s flux. Merging requires that both tokens are not in cooldown and still active.\\n\\nC. Reset the new (merged) token to accrue new flux.\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢â€‚Action: Call Voter.reset with the new token ID.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: Voter (\\"0x2279B7A0a67DB372996a5FaB50D91eAA73d2eBe6\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"reset\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [newTokenId]  \\nâ€¢â€‚Rationale: The reset call will call IVotingEscrow(veALCX).abstain and then IFluxToken(FLUX).accrueFlux(newTokenId) so that the new tokenâ€™s unclaimedFlux is increased by the FluxToken.accrueFlux logic.\\n\\nD. Query and verify the unclaimedFlux of the new token.\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚Tool: call_view_tool  \\nâ€¢â€‚Action: Call FluxToken.getUnclaimedFlux for the new token.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: FluxToken (\\"0x0165878A594ca255338adfa4d48449f69242Eb8F\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"getUnclaimedFlux\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [newTokenId]  \\nâ€¢â€‚Rationale: Compare the unclaimedFlux value (call it flux_new) to the flux recorded from the previous token. Ensure that flux_new is strictly greater than the flux value from the prior round. Save flux_new and set prevTokenId = newTokenId for the next iteration.\\n\\nâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€"},"tag_type":"PLANNER_STEP","stream_id":"stream_104","stream_complete":true}',
