    data: '{"type":"planner-step","data":{"tag_type":"planner_step","timestamp":"2025-10-14T15:26:28.505486+00:00","step_number":5,"content":"Step 4. (Final Assertion)\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚Tool: call_view_tool  \\nâ€¢â€‚Action: After the loop ends (after 10 iterations), call FluxToken.getUnclaimedFlux for the final token ID.  \\nâ€¢â€‚Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: FluxToken (\\"0x0165878A594ca255338adfa4d48449f69242Eb8F\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"getUnclaimedFlux\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [finalTokenId]  \\nâ€¢â€‚Rationale: Verify that the final unclaimedFlux is roughly linear with respect to the number of iterationsâ€”that is, it should be at least about ten times the baseline value (flux_baseline). This will provide evidence that unclaimedFlux grows repeatedly as hypothesized.\\n\\nâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€  \\nGeneral Notes and Considerations\\n\\nâ€¢â€‚All merge and reset actions require the veNFT to be in an active, non-cooldown state and not already voted (the Voter.reset function enforces onlyNewEpoch). Ensure that while performing the iterative loop you are not triggering any cooldown requirement or accidentally voting.\\n  \\nâ€¢â€‚The merge call in VotingEscrow internally calls IFluxToken(FLUX).mergeFlux which (after checking that msg.sender is veALCX) simply adds the unclaimedFlux from the source token to the target token and then zeroes out the source. Our plan exploits this to â€œaccumulateâ€ flux in the target token.\\n  \\nâ€¢â€‚Be sure to use functions.send_transaction_tool for all stateâ€changing calls (createLock, merge, reset) and use functions.call_view_tool to query unclaimedFlux.\\n  \\nâ€¢â€‚Track the returned token IDs and unclaimedFlux numbers between iterations so that you may compare them; log any discrepancy if the flux does not strictly increase.\\n  \\nâ€¢â€‚No actual claim (minting ERC-20 Flux tokens to an address) is requiredâ€”you only need to show that unclaimedFlux increases as predicted.\\n\\nâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€  \\nBy following these steps using the provided tools and using the deployed addresses, you will be able to test whether a user can grow the unclaimedFlux arbitrarily by the described procedure."},"tag_type":"PLANNER_STEP","stream_id":"stream_105","stream_complete":true}',
