    opcode: 1,
    data: '{"type":"planner-step","data":{"tag_type":"planner_step","timestamp":"2025-10-14T15:27:34.624072+00:00","step_number":3,"content":"Step 2. (Establish the Baseline)\\n\\nA. Create an initial (baseline) lock â€“ â€œprevious token.â€\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call VotingEscrow.createLock to generate a veNFT.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: VotingEscrow at \\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"createLock\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ initialAmount, lockDuration, maxLockEnabled ]  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒFor example:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒinitialAmount = 10e18 (10 tokens assuming 18 decimals),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒlockDuration = 31536000 seconds (1 year),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒmaxLockEnabled = false  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: This mints the first veNFT. Save the returned token id (call it tokenId_baseline).\\n\\nB. Retrieve the baseline token ID using a fallback method.\\n\\nSince a call to getTokenIds failed, we now call VotingEscrow.totalSupply, which returns the total number of veNFTs.  \\nâ€¢ Tool: call_view_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Query VotingEscrow.totalSupply.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: \\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"totalSupply\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: []  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: If tokens are minted sequentially and totalSupply returns an integer N, then the baseline token\'s id is N (assuming token IDs start at 1). Store this as tokenId_baseline.\\n\\nC. Reset the baseline token to accrue its initial unclaimedFlux.\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call Voter.reset on tokenId_baseline.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: Voter at \\"0x2279B7A0a67DB372996a5FaB50D91eAA73d2eBe6\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"reset\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ tokenId_baseline ]  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: This triggers the reset logic in Voter which calls VotingEscrow.abstain and then IFluxToken(FLUX).accrueFlux(tokenId_baseline), thereby setting the baseline unclaimedFlux.\\n\\nD. Query and record the baseline unclaimedFlux.\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: call_view_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call FluxToken.getUnclaimedFlux for tokenId_baseline.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: FluxToken at \\"0x0165878A594ca255338adfa4d48449f69242Eb8F\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"getUnclaimedFlux\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ tokenId_baseline ]  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: Save this value as flux_baseline for later comparison.\\n\\nâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€"},"tag_type":"PLANNER_STEP","stream_id":"stream_123","stream_complete":true}',
