    data: '{"type":"planner-step","data":{"tag_type":"planner_step","timestamp":"2025-10-14T15:27:34.624123+00:00","step_number":4,"content":"Step 3. (Iterative Merging Loop â€“ 10 Iterations)\\n\\nFor i = 1 to 10, perform these sub-steps:\\n\\nA. Create a â€œdustâ€ lock (new token).\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call VotingEscrow.createLock to mint a new â€œdustâ€ veNFT.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: VotingEscrow (\\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"createLock\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ dustAmount, shortLockDuration, maxLockEnabled ]  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒFor example, choose dustAmount = a very small value (e.g. 1 wei or a minimal accepted value),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒshortLockDuration = a valid duration (ensure the lock does not expire; for instance, several days in seconds),  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒmaxLockEnabled = false  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: This creates a new token (newTokenId) that will be the target for the merge.\\n\\nB. Merge the previous token into the new dust token.\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call VotingEscrow.merge to merge the previous token into the new token.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: VotingEscrow (\\"0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"merge\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ prevTokenId, newTokenId ]  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒFor the first iteration, prevTokenId = tokenId_baseline. For subsequent iterations, use the newTokenId from the previous iteration.  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: This calls IFluxToken(FLUX).mergeFlux which accumulates unclaimedFlux from the source (prevTokenId) to the target (newTokenId) and resets the sourceâ€™s flux.\\n\\nC. Reset the new merged token to accrue flux.\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: send_transaction_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call Voter.reset on the newTokenId.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: Voter (\\"0x2279B7A0a67DB372996a5FaB50D91eAA73d2eBe6\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"reset\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ newTokenId ]  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: This will trigger the Voter.reset logic to call VotingEscrow.abstain and then IFluxToken(FLUX).accrueFlux(newTokenId), causing the new tokenâ€™s unclaimedFlux to increase.\\n\\nD. Query the unclaimedFlux for the new token.\\n\\nâ€¢ Tool: call_view_tool  \\nâ€¢ Action: Call FluxToken.getUnclaimedFlux for newTokenId.  \\nâ€¢ Arguments:  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ contract_address: FluxToken (\\"0x0165878A594ca255338adfa4d48449f69242Eb8F\\")  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_name: \\"getUnclaimedFlux\\"  \\nâ€ƒâ€ƒâ€“ function_args: [ newTokenId ]  \\nâ€¢ Rationale: Retrieve flux_new from the new token and verify that it is strictly greater than the unclaimedFlux from the previous token. Record flux_new and update prevTokenId = newTokenId for the next iteration.\\n\\nâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€"},"tag_type":"PLANNER_STEP","stream_id":"stream_124","stream_complete":true}',
